The paper deals with the problem of localizing mobile agents in a network, which is a topic in multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves measuring distances between agents and using geometric approaches to update their locations, which falls under the category of networked sensing and control (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of virtual convex hulls to address the issue of agents not being able to find nearby nodes, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY).
